item.title: Building Real-Time Applications With SignalR & .NET 9 (full tutorial)
item.description:
Want to master Clean Architecture? Go here: https://bit.ly/3PupkOJ Want to unlock Modular Monoliths? Go here: https://bit.ly/3SXlzSt Get the source code here: https://www.patreon.com/milanjovanovic
Tired of polling your backend every 5 seconds for updates? In this full tutorial, I‚Äôll show you how to build real-time functionality into your .NET application using SignalR ‚Äî no page reloads, no polling, just smooth, live updates!
In this video, you'll learn:
- How to configure SignalR in your .NET backend - Building and exposing a SignalR Hub - Sending targeted updates to users (not just broadcasting!) - Securing SignalR connections with JWT authentication - Setting up a simple HTML/JS client to receive live messages - Bonus: Strongly-typed client methods for cleaner code
We‚Äôll build a small order tracking app that updates order statuses live in the browser as they change on the backend.
Whether you‚Äôre new to SignalR or looking to implement advanced features like authenticated hubs and user-specific notifications, this tutorial has you covered.
